Re: Writing kanji on a touch screen
by keatonatron » Sun 11.01.2009 9:02 pm Sure is. In fact, it's built right into windows. Just click the "IME pad" button on the Japanese IME toolbar (enabled through the "Region and Language" control panel).Edit: I should clarify, the IME handwriting tool allows you to look up a single character at a time... Are you looking for something that will allow you to write a whole paragraph and have it convert it into text for you? For that you'd probably need a program made for Japanese tablet PC's. Shouldn't be too hard to find if you search Google in Japanese.
