Re: Writing kanji on a touch screen
by Hyperworm » Tue 11.03.2009 6:12 pm Having just attempted to do entry of long strings of Japanese with XP, I found it actually doesn't work too badly (I'd never tried it before now).You use the IME handwriting pad, writing each character alternately in left and right boxes (multibox method). You can't tell how the recognition is going until the end. You hit Recog(nize), and then use the left and right arrow keys (or their analog on the handwriting pad itself) to step through each character to get to the ones that weren't recognized properly, and a candidates list is displayed sort of like the one you get with regular keyboard entry, except it contains the best handwriting matches.I'm not sure if there's an easy way to call up the handwriting pad and make it stay up. :s
